# `tm mcp` must start cleanly in a repo where the ledger isn't initialized.
# Once a harness has registered the `teammemory` MCP server globally (Codex
# stores MCP servers in ~/.codex/config.toml; Claude Code stores them in
# .mcp.json), every session — including ones in repos the user never ran
# `tm init` in — spawns `tm mcp`. The server must serve degraded (each tool
# returns an actionable IsError pointing to `tm init`) instead of exiting
# non-zero, so the harness doesn't show a failing-server warning in every
# unrelated repo.
#
# Empty stdin closes immediately; the stdio MCP loop reads EOF and exits 0.
# The historical bug was that openEnv's "no ledger" error short-circuited
# the command before the server ever started, returning exit 1.
exec tm mcp
! stderr 'no ledger'
